title: Japan Export Prices
description: Export Prices in Japan increased to 133.60 points in October from 131.90 points in September of 2022. Export Prices in Japan averaged 134.07 points from 1960 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 207.30 points in October of 1982 and a record low of 84.10 points in July of 2012. In Japan, Export Prices correspond to the rate of change in the prices of goods and services sold by residents of that country to foreign buyers. Export Prices are heavily affected by exchange rates. This page provides - Japan Export Prices - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Bank of Japan
